HOW TO RUN

-- using jar files
   goto jar files folder, open terminal inside it

	to run the server
		java -jar ChatServer.java

	to run a client
		java -jar ChatClient.java 
		or
		java -jar ChatClient.jar -cp ./lib/AbsoluteLayout.jar

	to run another client
		open a new terminal and type the same command
		java -jar ChatClient.jar

-- using netbeans

	please watch the video HowToRun.wmv

********************************************************

 	I found that it is possible to run both server and the client without generating stub and only with copied interface into Client from Server.

	And according to "Stack Overflow", Since rmic 1.2 onwards, Java doesn't generate skeleton class any more. 
	New JRMP protocol supported for RMI has got rid of the use of skeleton files.
	http://stackoverflow.com/questions/18290836/when-is-the-skeleton-object-created-in-rmi

